MACROS	     this file describes several macros that have been defined
	     in ezlib.h

    The file ezlib.h contains a few macros to 1) in general make life a
little easier, and 2) to facilitate working with ez.lib.

    As mentioned in OpenLibs.doc, there are several numbers defined to
specify which libraries to open in a call to openlibs().  They are:

		    #define GFX 	0x0001
		    #define INTUI	0x0002
		    #define INTUITION	0x0002
		    #define ARP 	0x0004
		    #define DFONT	0x0008
		    #define DISKFONT	0x0008
		    #define TRANSLATOR	0x0010
		    #define ICONBASE	0x0080
		    #define REXX	0x0100

		    #define ALL_LIBS	0xffff

    As you can see, they are readily or'ed together to open several
libraries at once.  Or you can use the define ALL_LIBS to open all the
libraries (probably overkill).  ALL_LIBS is more useful for a cleanup
procedure so that it doesn't have to know about which libraries are opened,
it can just do CloseLibs(ALL_LIBS) and everything that was actually
opened is closed. Not much else to say here.

