    Next there is the MSG() macro taken and modified from an old
Transactor.  This is a simple macro to put out a string onto whatever
output stream may be attatched to your program (i.e. whether from WorkBench
or the CLI).  Use as follows :

	   MSG("Something happened.\n");

    Again, it will simply dump out a string onto your output stream.  Note
that it is NOT the same as a printf() call and does NOT take formatting
arguments as does printf().

